All done. Here's what was implemented:

**`internal/tui/` (8 new files):**
- `keys.go` — `KeyMap` struct with all 7 bindings; implements `help.KeyMap` interface
- `styles.go` — `Styles` struct with all lipgloss styles; `NewStyles()` is the only place calling `lipgloss.NewStyle()`
- `card.go` — renders one MR: title (truncated), author/age/phase/round-trips, reviewer pills with icons (⏳💬🔄✓)
- `column.go` — one column per phase; header shows name+count; empty-state message; focus management (Up/Down with wrap)
- `board.go` — 4 columns joined horizontally; Left/Right navigation preserves row index (clamped); initial focus on first non-empty column
- `footer.go` — wraps `help.Model` for the keybinding bar
- `spinner.go` — wraps `bubbles/spinner.Model`; propagated only when loading
- `model.go` — root model: loading/board/error state machine; AltScreen set only here; `FetchResultMsg`/`FetchErrMsg` custom messages; `open`/`xdg-open` for browser launch

**`cmd/mrboard/main.go`** — wires config → gitlab client → `tui.New()` → `tea.NewProgram(m).Run()`

All quality gates pass (`go build ./...`, `go vet ./...`, `go test ./...`). Package boundaries verified: domain=stdlib only, config/gitlab=no charmbracelet, tui=only charmbracelet importer.

